ExCnt.EX: Walking there , the glitter of the lake came up brokenly to the eye , through the beech-tree branches , that lay like sprays of maidenhair beneath them ; and over the hill and down to the water 's edge and far away among the grey beech stems , the bluebells ran like a blue mist through all the wood .
The lobed leaves , tending to occur in threes , are reminiscent of ferns , some say of maidenhair .
Maidenhairs, tree ferns, stags, elks, common ground ferns.
He headed for a short , thick clump of maidenhair fern .
The delicate fronds of maidenhair ferns , tucked in limestone pockets , fan out over the babbling stream .
